f(x)  = \sum_{k=1}^n k x^k 
g(x)  = \sum_{k=1}^n (n-k) x^k 
\begin{align} f(x)x^{-n} &=\sum_{k=1}^n k x^{k-n}\\ &=\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} (n-k) x^{-k}\\ &=\sum_{k=0}^{n} (n-k) x^{-k}\\ &=n+\sum_{k=1}^{n} (n-k) x^{-k}\\ &=n+g(1/x)\\ \end{align} 
f(1/x)x^n = n+g(x)
g(x) = x^n f(1/x) - n
